  "abstract": "Groundnut (Atachis hypogaea L.) is one of the important\r\nlegume crops of both the tropical and temperate regions of the\r\nworld. About 77% of the worlds total groundnut area is in the\r\nsemi-arid tropics producing 65% of the total production. Asia\r\nproduces 10.9 million tonnes, Africa 5.2 million tonnes, North and Centrel America 2.0 million tonnes and South America 0.8 million tonnes.",
